A fire has broken out at the FH Odendaal Hospital in Limpopo. The blaze apparently started in the COVID-19 ward. Health MEC in the province Dr Phopi Ramathuba speaks on this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - At least two people have died after a fire broke out at the FH Odendaal Hospital in Modimolle, Limpopo. The blaze apparently started in the COVID-19 ward. READ:Â Fire breaks out at Limpopo hospital The Province's Health MEC, Dr Phophi Ramathuba, says the nurses evacuated several patients. The cause of the fire has not yet been established.